AN ACT relating to regional transportation commissions; revising
provisions relating to the security in operations of a
regional transportation commission; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, a board of county commissioners may by ordinance create
2 a regional transportation commission if a streets and highways plan has been
3 adopted as part of the master plan by the county or regional planning commission.
4 (NRS 277A.170) Existing law authorizes a regional transportation commission to
5 provide for and maintain such security in operations as is necessary for the
6 protection of persons and property under its jurisdiction and control. (NRS
7 277A.260) Existing law further provides that it is a misdemeanor for a person to
8 willfully use profane, offensive or indecent language or engage in any quarrel in
9 any public conveyance, or interfere with or annoy any passenger therein, or fail to
10 leave any such conveyance upon demand after having refused to pay the proper
11 fare. (NRS 203.100)
12 Section 1 of this bill authorizes any designated security personnel employed by
13 a regional transportation commission to remove from a vehicle or other property of
14 the commission any person who is engaged in any such conduct.
